  "text": "Following a qualitative argument, consider that the Sun currently spins about 10 times slower than it once did (Bouvier 2013; [CITATION_1] . Accordingly, its wind has cumulatively carried away 10 times the Sun's current angular momentum. Only 1%, on average, of that wind-driven torque needs to have acted perpendicular to the spin axis over the past 4.5 Gyr for the Sun's current orientation to differ by several degrees from its primordial orientation.",
